                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know that NPCs treat the party as a group encounter, but does anyone understand the mechanics of hate in EQ2 and if so, whether it changes going through each tier of adventurer level?
<br />

<br />
Right now my experience has been when the 29 guardian tank pulls, he almost never loses aggro. In the ultra rare instances he loses aggro, he has no snap aggro capability and the character getting hit needs to be able to withstand the beatdown (with or without healing) for at least 6 seconds and sometimes the rest of the fight. I forget that I can blink my illusionist, but my experience with my rogue, who can at least take a few hits, is that not only is a guardian unable to snap aggro back, evade has never once given me snap aggro loss. I always turn off attack and take my lumps until the mob finally turns around.
<br />

<br />
Has this been everyone else's experience as well? I know the goal is to not get aggro, but there doesn't seem to be any way of reaching the redline without overshooting it significantly.
<br />

<br />
Natten</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
